au.com.redboxresearchdata.fascinator.plugins

Class JsonHarvestQueueConsumer

  • java.lang.Object
    • au.com.redboxresearchdata.fascinator.plugins.JsonHarvestQueueConsumer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JsonHarvestQueueMXBean, com.googlecode.fascinator.common.messaging.GenericListener, Runnable, javax.jms.MessageListener

    public class JsonHarvestQueueConsumer
extends Object
implements com.googlecode.fascinator.common.messaging.GenericListener, JsonHarvestQueueMXBean
    A Listener that harvests incoming JSON objects. Basic behavior is: 1. Load up the harvesters. 2. Wait for incoming JSON. 3. Determine if incoming JSON has type. 4. Process the JSON document. 5. Determine if there are any failed items, putting these into the "failed" map, which can be inspected and reprocessed through JMX.
    Author:
    Shilo Banihit
